# Barcode Scanner (Standalone)

This module is developed **independently** of the main MacroTrack app. Do not wire it into the Log tab, Kitchen Mode, server, or `shared/types` until the integration phase.

## Public API

- **`scanWithCamera()`** — iOS/Android only. Opens camera scanner. Returns `Promise<BarcodeScanResult | null>`.
- **`scanFromImage(uri: string, options?: { type?: string; name?: string })`** — All platforms. Scans barcode from image URI. Returns `Promise<BarcodeScanResult | null>`. On iOS, pass `type`/`name` when available for server upload.

Result type: `BarcodeScanResult { gtin: string; raw: string; format: string }`. GTIN is normalized to 13-digit (e.g. UPC-A zero-padded).

## Platform

- **Camera scanner**: iOS and Android only. Use native `launchScanner()` when available (fastest); fallback to in-app `CameraView` with target overlay. On web, do not show or call camera — hide the option.
- **Image upload**: Available on all platforms. **Web**: client-side decode (canvas + @zxing/library). **Android**: expo-camera `scanFromURLAsync(uri, barcodeTypes)`. **iOS**: upload image to `POST /api/barcode/scan` (server decodes with sharp + @zxing/library). Use `expo-image-picker` then `scanFromImage(uri, { type, name })`.

## Tech

- `expo-camera` (barcode scanning, `launchScanner`, `scanFromURLAsync` on Android)
- `expo-image-picker` (pick image for upload flow)
- `@zxing/library` (web: decode from image; server: decode from uploaded image for iOS)

## Testing

- **Maintain tests** when changing the barcode feature: add or update tests for new/updated behavior.
- **Test location**: `mobile/features/barcode/__tests__/`. Unit tests for `gtin.ts` and `scanner.ts` (with mocked `expo-camera`).
- **Run tests**: From repo root, `cd mobile && npm test`. Uses Jest in Node for barcode tests (see `mobile/jest.config.js`).
- **Adding tests**: New logic in `gtin.ts` or result handling in `scanner.ts` should have corresponding tests in `__tests__/*.test.ts`. Keep mocks minimal; prefer testing pure functions (e.g. `normalizeToGTIN`) directly.

For full scope, file layout, and validation steps see **BUILD_GUIDE.md** → "Standalone: Barcode Scanner".
